# Premium Studio Website Rules

## TypeScript & Structure
- Always use TypeScript.
- Prefer reusable components in `src/components/ui`, `src/components/layout`, and `src/components/sections`.
- Keep components small and clean.
- Use semantic HTML (`header`, `nav`, `main`, `section`, `footer`, `article`, `blockquote`).

## Content & Data
- Keep all pricing, service, work, and testimonial content in `src/data/` files.
- Keep brand name, nav, hero copy, and CTAs in `src/data/siteConfig.ts`.
- Do not hardcode repeated content inside components.
- Do not add fake backend logic.

## Design
- Mobile-first responsive design.
- Premium spacing, typography, and visual hierarchy.
- Visual concept: **"Digital systems in motion"** — flowing connection lines, animated nodes, system diagrams, kinetic typography.
- Super premium dark theme: near-black, charcoal surfaces, soft white text, selective accent blue/violet/green.
- Use `panel-surface`, `gradient-border`, `editorial-headline`, `label-mono` utility classes — not generic glass card grids.
- No generic startup/SaaS template look.
- Every section should feel like a different scene in one story — use asymmetry and overlapping layers.
- Make CTAs clear and repeated throughout pages.
- Make the website easy to expand later.

## Animation (Framer Motion)
- Keep animation smooth and performance-safe.
- Prefer `transform` and `opacity` animations over layout-heavy animations.
- Respect `prefers-reduced-motion`.
- Use scroll reveals, subtle hovers, and staggered entrances — avoid excessive motion.

## CSS
- Use Tailwind CSS utilities and shared classes in `src/styles/index.css`.
- Avoid messy one-off CSS unless necessary for effects (noise, grid, marquee).
- No horizontal scrolling on any breakpoint.

## Performance
- No WebGL, 3D libraries, or heavy canvas effects.
- Use CSS gradients and lightweight motion.
- Prefer placeholder gradients/CSS visuals over large image assets.

## Expansion
- New pages go in `src/pages/` and are registered in `src/app/App.tsx`.
- New sections go in `src/components/sections/`.
- New reusable UI goes in `src/components/ui/`.
